## Web Research Complete

**Queries**: 4 searches executed
**Sources**: 6 relevant sources found
**Artifact**: `/home/asiri/.archon/workspaces/alexsiri7/reli/artifacts/runs/f58fd5bb22e46ab9a470c2d0f5f76887/web-research.md`

### Key Findings

- **Root cause confirmed**: The "Validate Railway secrets" step (added in commit `eae2134`) hard-fails with `exit 1` when `RAILWAY_TOKEN`, `RAILWAY_STAGING_SERVICE_ID`, `RAILWAY_STAGING_ENVIRONMENT_ID`, or `RAILWAY_STAGING_URL` are not set in the repo's GitHub Secrets.
- **GitHub limitation**: Secrets cannot be referenced directly in job-level `if:` conditions — the `secrets` context is unsupported there, so a "secrets gate" job is the only reliable way to skip an entire job based on secret availability.
- **Recommended fix**: Add a `secrets-gate` job that checks `RAILWAY_TOKEN` and outputs `ok=true/false`, then add `needs: [secrets-gate]` and `if: needs.secrets-gate.outputs.ok == 'true'` to `deploy-staging`. When `deploy-staging` is skipped, `staging-e2e` and `deploy-production` are automatically skipped too (not failed), keeping CI green.
- **Railway API**: The existing `serviceInstanceUpdate` + `serviceInstanceDeploy` GraphQL mutations are correct per Railway docs — no changes needed there.

### Gaps

- Cannot determine whether the secrets were intentionally removed or never configured — the fix applies either way.

Sources:
- [Skipping Jobs in GitHub Actions when Secrets are Unavailable](https://cloudtruth.com/blog/skipping-jobs-in-github-actions-when-secrets-are-unavailable-securely-inject-configuration-secrets-into-github/)
- [Workflow syntax for GitHub Actions - GitHub Docs](https://docs.github.com/actions/using-workflows/workflow-syntax-for-github-actions)
- [Using secrets in GitHub Actions - GitHub Docs](https://docs.github.com/actions/security-guides/encrypted-secrets)
- [Secrets cannot be used to condition job runs · Issue #520 · actions/runner](https://github.com/actions/runner/issues/520)
- [Manage Services with the Public API | Railway Docs](https://docs.railway.com/integrations/api/manage-services)
- [GitHub Actions PR Environment | Railway Guides](https://docs.railway.com/guides/github-actions-pr-environment)
